deselectAll(25.10)                                          deselectAll(25.10)

Name
       deselectAll - Deselects all selected nets

Syntax
       deselectAll

       [-help]

       Deselects  all selected nets. Once the nets are deselected, they are no
       longer highlighted in the design display window. Use this command after
       selecting one or more nets.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description of the deselectAll  command.  For  a
              detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man deselectAll

Related Information
              * selectNet

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

